What’s In It For You?


As a System Developer in the ID Software Development group at CBN, you will have the chance to develop, broaden and apply your System Administration skillset as you work on highly customized, complex security solutions for our government customers throughout North America, the Caribbean and around the world. When travel is safe again you’ll even have the chance to travel to these locations during the deployment and stabilization periods. The Caribbean in February? Yes, please!


CBN is an organization that is predicated upon continuous improvement, and that extends to our employees. We want to see you grow and will support you in that pursuit. You’ll also get to play with some pretty cool technologies along the way!

What Will You Do?


You’ll be responsible for the full cycle of configuration and virtualization of server hardware, deployment and tune-up of OS and system software, writing scripts to automate deployment of CBN and third party software during the development cycle and then supporting the system through the deployment and stabilization period. More specifically, you will:

Create and maintain system environments. Develop Puppet classes and templates to automate server environments installation and configuration; deploy software that ensures compatible versions of frontend and backend database software and configuration; maintain functional development and test environments; troubleshoot system issues and liaise with developers and testers to pinpoint issues and provide fixes.

Deploy systems. Work with system architect to plan system capacity and calculate the hardware requirements for the size of the database and system required and then install and configure the production system locally in advance of shipping to customer site. Write database creation and change scripts to support database development, test and deployment. Some travel to customer site for deployment of hardware and system launch which may include providing training and support to Developers and local service providers.

Provide system support through stabilization period. Stabilize the system and fix performance issues by monitoring and responding to production alerts pro-actively and provide support for any issues. Tune live systems and deploy software updates as required. Write system documentation and then handover to the Support team once stabilized.



What Will Help You Succeed?
Success in this position will require a diversified set of skills, attained either through education or relevant work experience. Beneficial technical knowledge sets are listed below – but don’t despair if you don’t have them all – so long as you are passionate about technology and have an appetite for learning, we still want to hear from you! 




